        <h4>WHAT DOES THE FUTURE HOLD?</h4>
        <p>A 4-bin waste and recycling system will become the standard for households across Victoria by 2030.</p>
        <p>A container deposit scheme is to be set up by 2022-23, which will allow people to swap empty cans and bottles for cash.</p>
        <p>The Victorian government is investing almost $100 million in order to strengthen the waste and recycling industry, which means growth of the local industry, creation of more jobs and new technologies coming up.</p>
        <p>A new waste and recycling Act and a waste authority will be set up to put a stop to unsafe/illegal storage of waste.</p>
        <p>The bin information presented below is of the City of Monash. However, you can check out your local council at <a href="https://knowyourcouncil.vic.gov.au/councils" target="_blank" style="color:#2e8b57; text-decoration:underline;">Know Your Council</a> website.</p>
        <p class="text-bold">Click on the below bins to find out which waste goes into which bins.</p>
